Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and mince @shallots{2}. Mince or grate @garlic{4%cloves}. Peel @carrots{4}, then thinly slice on an angle. Dice @roma tomatoes{2}. Roughly chop @dried apricots{2%oz}. Finely chop @cilantro{1/2%oz}. Drain and rinse @chickpeas{26.8%oz}. Cut lemons into quarters.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the shallots and half the garlic. Cook, stirring, until just softened, ~{1-3%minutes}. Stir in 1 1/2 cups water, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then add @couscous{1%cup}. Cover, remove from heat, and set aside.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Italian chicken sausage{18%oz} and half the @Turkish spice blend{2%tbsp}, breaking up meat into pieces. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add carrots and chickpeas. Cook until veggies soften and begin to brown, about ~{5%minutes}. Add a big pinch of salt and all of the remaining shallots, garlic, and @Turkish spice blend{2%tbsp}. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, about ~{2%minutes}. Meanwhile, stir together 2/3 cup water and @chicken stock concentrate{2} in a #small bowl{}.

Pour stock mixture into pan. Stir in sausage and tomatoes. Bring to a gentle simmer, then cover pan. Cook until liquid is slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}. Meanwhile, in another small bowl, mix @sour cream{4%tbsp}, @hot sauce{2%tsp}(to taste), and a pinch of salt. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture has a drizzling consistency.

> TIP: Use a piece of aluminum foil to cover your pan if it doesn't have a lid.

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}, then stir in @butter{2%tbsp}, a squeeze or two of lemon, and half the cilantro. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Divide between plates. Top with tagine. Drizzle with crema. Garnish with apricots and remaining cilantro. Serve with remaining lemon quarters on the side for squeezing over.